cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about a neural network module designed for conditional dependency modeling in natural language processing tasks, specifically query-based summarization. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on the intersection of computer science and linguistics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and knowledge graph reasoning, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), respectively.
